{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "name", "icon": "SOP/name", "tags": "attrs, string", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Name"], "extent": [0, 9]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates a ", {"type": "q", "text": ["naming"]}, " attribute on points or primitives allowing you\nto refer to them easily, similar to groups."], "extent": [90, 207]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Naming points or primitives"], "extent": [207, 241], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node sets an attribute (called ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, " by default) on the selected\npoints/primitives to a certain value. For example, you can select a\nsingle face, or small set of faces, on some polygonal geometry, and\n", {"type": "q", "text": ["name"]}, " it ", {"type": "code", "text": ["foo"]}, " (that is, create a primitive attribute ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, " with the\nvalue ", {"type": "code", "text": ["foo"]}, ") on the faces. You can then refer to the primitives in\nsubsequent nodes using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["@name=foo"]}, "."], "extent": [241, 624]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is very similar to ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/model/groups", "type": "link", "text": ["groups"], "fullpath": "/model/groups.html"}, ": using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["@name=foo"]}, " is\nsimilar to creating a group ", {"type": "code", "text": ["foo"]}, " and referring to it using ", {"type": "code", "text": ["@foo"]}, ".\nHowever, name attributes have two differences from groups:"], "extent": [624, 821]}, {"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 4, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Names are more efficient than groups. For example, you can assign\n    different names to hundreds or thousands of individual faces, while\n    creating hundreds of groups, each with a single member, would be\n    problematic."], "extent": [821, 1054]}, {"blevel": 4, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": ["Names enforce the constraint that each primitive can only have\n    one name value at a time (that is, a primitive can\u2019t be included\n    in both ", {"type": "code", "text": ["@name=foo"]}, " and ", {"type": "code", "text": ["@name=bar"]}, "), whereas a primitive can be\n    a member of multiple groups. This constraint may be useful in\n    some workflows."], "extent": [1054, 1346]}], "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Mantra uses named primitives to determine how to bind volumes to\nshaders during rendering.  The ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/volumevop", "type": "link", "text": ["Volume Vop node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/volumevop.html"}, "\nuses named primitives to determine binding if ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Autobind"]}, " is on."], "extent": [1346, 1546]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Renaming existing named groups"], "extent": [1546, 1583], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["In addition to assigning names to points and primitives, you can\nalso use this node to rename existing named groups, using the\n", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Global"]}, ", ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["From"]}, ", and ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["To"]}, " parameters. This works like\nthe Attrib String Edit node. See\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit", "type": "link", "text": ["the help for Attrib String Edit"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit.html"}, "\nfor more information."], "extent": [1583, 1888]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1888, 1900], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute"], "extent": [1900, 1912], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The name of the attribute to create or edit. The default is\n        ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, ", the attribute name mantra and the\n        ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/volumevop", "type": "link", "text": ["Volume Vop node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/volumevop.html"}, " look for."], "extent": [1912, 2090]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Class"], "extent": [2090, 2097], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether to name points, primitives, or vertices."], "extent": [2097, 2151]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Name from Group"], "extent": [2151, 2168], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Assigns the name attribute to the corresponding name of the group\n    the point or primitive is part of.  If it is part of more than one\n    group, the behaviour is undefined.  The idea is to provide\n    the inverse to the Partition SOP."], "extent": [2168, 2411]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group Mask"], "extent": [2411, 2423], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When naming from groups, only groups that match this pattern will\n    be used.  This avoids other material groups overwriting your\n    desired partition group."], "extent": [2423, 2592]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Namings"], "extent": [2592, 2611], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of naming attributes to create. Click the\n    ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "BUTTONS/add", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/BUTTONS/add.html"}, " Add icon."], "extent": [2611, 2706]}, {"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Group"], "extent": [2706, 2717], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["The list of points/primitives to create/edit the attribute on.\n                Normally this is filled in by Houdini from the viewport selection.\n                See ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/model/groups#manual", "type": "link", "text": ["specifying groups"], "fullpath": "/model/groups.html#manual", "fragment": "#manual"}, " for information on\n                the format for specifying point and attribute numbers manually."], "extent": [2717, 3040]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Name"], "extent": [3040, 3050], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 16, "text": ["The attribute value to set on the points/primitives in the group."], "extent": [3050, 3141]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["For example, if ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Attribute"]}, " is ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, " and this parameter is\n        ", {"type": "code", "text": ["foo"]}, ", Houdini will create a ", {"type": "code", "text": ["name"]}, " attribute on each of the\n        points/primitives listed in ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Group"]}, " and set it to ", {"type": "code", "text": ["foo"]}, "."], "extent": [3141, 3352]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable"], "extent": [3352, 3360], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether to create/edit the attribute. This parameter lets you\n    animate the operation of this node."], "extent": [3360, 3467]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You can use the following parameters to rename existing named groups.\nSee ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit", "type": "link", "text": ["Attrib String Edit"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit.html"}, " for more information."], "extent": [3467, 3611]}, {"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Global"], "extent": [3611, 3619], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When this option is on, the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["From"]}, " pattern is replaced for each\n    occurrence in the string. When off, only the first occurrence is\n    replaced."], "extent": [3619, 3777]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["From"], "extent": [3777, 3783], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The string pattern to rename."], "extent": [3783, 3822]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["To"], "extent": [3822, 3826], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The replacement pattern for the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["From"]}, " string."], "extent": [3826, 3880]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [3880, 3889], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/attribstringedit.html"}], "extent": [3889, 3920]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/volumevop", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/volumevop.html"}], "extent": [3920, 3943]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/groupsfromname", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/groupsfromname.html"}], "extent": [3943, 3972]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Name"], "summary": ["Creates a ", {"type": "q", "text": ["naming"]}, " attribute on points or primitives allowing you\nto refer to them easily, similar to groups."]}